We ended up ordering the Shrimp Work bowl and Tennessee Hot Chicken.  The Shrimp Wok rice bowl had fresh ingredients and had a great flavor, but should have ordered white rice instead of brown rice. Just personal preference. The Tennessee Hot Chicken is essentially a couple of chicken breasts with skin, fried and tossed in habanero honey sauce. It was surprisingly good, but could have used a little more heat, and the coleslaw was solid.  The place operated like a well oiled machine and service was pretty good for the lunch rush.

Ive dined here a lot since September. Generally good, upscale family/diner style restaurant. The waiting staff are impeccable in every way, however, today i ordered soup with a sandwich to follow. So did my friend. We specified that we wanted the soup first followed by the sandwich. The sandwich arrived half way through the soup which meant we had this awkward rearranging of the table while we were trying to finish our matzo ball. I said nothing. I should have maybe. I even left a good tip. I hate feeling rushed and that was exactly how i felt by having the main course forced upon us during the first course. Now I know this is not fine dining, but please, make it look as though you want us to take our time. The waiting staff asked about 5 times how things were tasting but maybe they could have paid attention to the flow of the meal. I will give Doc Bs another go. I want to like them. But I wont extend my patience indefinitely.
